================================================================================
üé® MANDATORY DESIGN SYSTEM - CYBERPUNK VIBE
================================================================================

The environment includes a pre-configured "Cyberpunk" design system with:
- Deep dark background (#181c20)
- Neon cyan primary color (#2dd4bf)
- Space Grotesk font for headings
- JetBrains Mono font for code/numbers
- Futuristic glowing effects

================================================================================
üî• REQUIRED USAGE - AppShell Component
================================================================================

EVERY page component MUST wrap its content in <AppShell>:

```tsx
import { AppShell } from '@/components/app/AppShell';

export default function MyPage() {
  return (
    <AppShell>
      {/* Your page content here */}
    </AppShell>
  );
}
```

AppShell provides:
- Full-screen dark background with network grid
- Ambient glow effects (top-left cyan, bottom-right purple)
- Centered responsive container
- Fade-in entrance animation

================================================================================
üõ†Ô∏è UTILITY CLASSES - USE THESE FOR INSTANT CYBERPUNK STYLE
================================================================================

The system provides pre-built classes for common patterns:

1. TEXT EFFECTS:
   .text-gradient
   - Cyan-to-teal gradient text effect
   - Use for headings, important numbers, brand text
   
   Example:
   <h1 className="text-gradient text-6xl font-bold">
     Cyber Counter
   </h1>

2. BUTTONS:
   .btn-brand
   - Rounded pill button with neon glow
   - Gradient background (cyan ‚Üí teal)
   - Hover: scale up + enhanced glow
   - Active: scale down feedback
   
   .btn-brand-outline
   - Transparent with cyan border
   - Hover: fills with cyan tint + glow
   
   Example:
   <button className="btn-brand px-8 py-4 text-lg font-medium">
     <Play className="w-5 h-5 mr-2" />
     Start Timer
   </button>

3. PANELS/CARDS:
   .glass-panel
   - Dark card with glass morphism effect
   - Subtle gradient background
   - Border glow
   - Use for all content containers
   
   Example:
   <div className="glass-panel p-8 space-y-4">
     <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold">Stats</h2>
     <p className="text-muted-foreground">Your data here</p>
   </div>

4. GLOW EFFECTS:
   .glow-primary
   - Multi-layer box-shadow with cyan glow
   - Use sparingly for emphasis (numbers, active states)
   
   Example:
   <div className="text-8xl font-mono font-bold text-gradient glow-primary">
     {count}
   </div>

5. BACKGROUNDS:
   .bg-gradient-radial
   - Subtle radial gradient emanating from center
   - Use as overlay for sections needing extra depth

